00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:08,080
Walk.

263
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:14,080
Here's the deal: if I Lose with your jury,
you do the explaining.

264
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:16,880
Your Honor, may I continue?

265
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:20,200
We'd Like to excuse Jurors three, four and six.

266
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:15,480
Hi. You're home early for a change.

267
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,240
Your mother called.

268
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:24,160
She has her ''bad feeling''.

269
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:31,120
Every now and then, she gets one right.

270
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:34,800
You okay?

271
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:39,000
Something's up.

272
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:42,600
They deliberated for 38 minutes.

273
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:49,680
Oh, honey, I'm sorry.

274
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:56,440
What the hell did they expect?
The man is as guilty as can be.

275
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:59,680
Wasn't a jury anywhere gonna Let him off.

276
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,680
Yeah.

277
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:04,920
Except one.

278
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:06,280
What?

279
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:13,600
Not fucking guilty!

280
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:16,440
Oh, my God! You lying...

281
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:17,960
sack of shit!

282
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:20,120
Thirty-eight minutes, my jury!

283
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,560
Thirty-eight minutes!

284
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:27,360
- You did it!
- My jury! I'm too good!

285
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:34,200
- Glad you could stick around.
- It's your dime.

286
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:35,440
Sorry to keep you waiting.

287
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:39,000
Mr. Milton got pinned down in Indonesia
longer than expected.

288
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,960
Good morning, Caprice.

289
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,160
Good morning, Mr. Heath.

290
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,520
Your messages.

291
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:49,800
Not bad, huh?

292
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,480
You can play it cool if you want...

293
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:55,720
but when I first walked in, my jaw was on the floor.

294
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,320
This is our home office.

295
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,000
We have many international arrangements...

296
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:04,720
so Mr. Milton spends a great deal of his time in the air.

297
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:06,280
Three o'clock, we got the Greeks.

298
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:08,280
Am I a good cop or a bad cop?

299
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:10,120
We may not need a good cop.

300
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,320
I Love it.

301
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:16,080
In addition to our corporate clients we're
representing 25 foreign countries:

302
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:19,280
The Mideast, the Balkans, Central America, West Africa...

303
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:21,920
Interesting work, but travel-intensive.

304
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:18,560
Behind you.

305
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,280
I'm sorry.

306
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:23,160
Please. Kevin Lomax.

307
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:24,840
John Milton.

308
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,280
Nice to meet you.

309
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:32,800
So?

310
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:35,720
Have we been treating you well?

311
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:36,920
Very well, thank you.

312
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:39,000
And your wife, she's had a good time?

313
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:42,600
She sure has. It's been great.
The whole thing's been great.

314
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:46,720
That's our secret:

315
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,720
Kill you with kindness.

316
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,720
What's your secret?

317
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,880
I couldn't say.

318
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:56,680
You were a prosecutor.

319
00:21:56,760 --> 00:22:00,480
Out of law school.
Five years in the Jacksonville D. A. 's office.

320
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:04,960
Sixty-four straight convictions.

321
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,840
What a number!

322
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:10,120
I Like to be in court.

323
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:12,160
I didn't plea out a lot.

324
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,320
What's that Like?

325
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,600
One day you put them away,
the next you set them free.

326
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:20,240
Takes a little getting used to.

327
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,960
Pays better, though, doesn't it?

328
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:23,680
Yes, it does.

329
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:29,720
That math teacher, the Gettys case...
now I hear you were brilliant.

330
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:32,320
Prosecutor dropped the ball.

331
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:33,480
Really?

332
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,000
You think your guy was guilty?

333
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:37,360
I didn't say that.

334
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:38,720
What'd you say?

335
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:41,240
How's this:

336
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:44,680
I began the case with a clear conscience.

337
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,920
I was sure you had a secret.

338
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,720
The men's room.

339
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,600
Upstairs men's room in the Duval County courthouse.

340
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:04,360
There's a hole in the wall to the next room.

341
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:07,320
I spent five years Listening to juries deliberate.

342
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:09,240
- I Love it.
- Love it all you want.

343
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:10,600
Just don't repeat it.

344
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:14,160
I'm not sure the Florida Bar Association would appreciate it.

345
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,200
My lips are sealed.

346
00:23:16,760 --> 00:23:19,800
You don't really want to go back to Florida, do you?

347
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:25,320
Walk with me.

348
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:47,280
What do you think?

349
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:50,400
Some people can't handle it.

350
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,200
It's peaceful.

351
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:56,520
My sentiments exactly.

352
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:03,000
Fill in the resume for me.
Tell me, your father, what does he do?

353
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:06,880
I never got to know my father.
He passed away before I was born.

354
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,520
My mother raised me. Just the two of us.

355
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:10,960
She never remarried?

356
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:13,200
She wasn't married the first time.

357
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:16,680
That can't be easy in a town Like Gainesville, can it?

358
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:19,680
I don't think it's easy anywhere.

359
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:23,160
Holy shit!

360
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:26,560
Different when you're Looking down, isn't it?

361
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:28,360
Yes, it is.

362
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,600
Oh, my God.

363
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:32,280
Your mother...

364
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:34,000
what's she Like?

365
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:37,400
She's a preacher's daughter. She's tough.

366
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:41,080
She's worked in a poultry plant
for as long as I can remember.

367
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:45,240
She's got a church she really Likes,
so she's usually there or they go out...

368
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:47,320
They do a lot of volunteer work.

369
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:51,080
''Behold, I send you out as sheep amidst the wolves. ''

370
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:54,080
So they say.

371
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:56,080
It didn't rub off?

372
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:57,920
The Book? The Church?

373
00:24:58,280 --> 00:24:59,920
No, I'm on parole.

374
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:02,600
Early release for time served.

375
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:08,720
A lot of potential clients down there.

376
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,680
Are we negotiating?

377
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:12,720
Always.

378
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:16,440
Can I ask you a question, then?

379
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:19,760
Why do you need a criminal department?

380
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:23,680
Our clients break the law Like anyone else.

381
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:30,400
I'm just tired of sending their business across the street.

382
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:34,120
- Are you offering me a job?
- I'm thinking about it.

383
00:25:35,920 --> 00:25:39,240
I know you've got talent.
I knew that before you got here.

384
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:43,120
It's just the other thing I wonder about.

385
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:45,800
What thing?

386
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:49,040
Pressure.

387
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:52,320
It changes everything. Pressure.

388
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:55,640
Some people, you squeeze them, they focus.

389
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,480
Others fold.

390
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,960
Can you summon your talent at will?

391
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:04,640
Can you deliver on a deadline?

392
00:26:06,080 --> 00:26:07,720
Can you sleep at night?

393
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:11,080
When do we talk about money?

394
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:12,280
Money?

395
00:26:16,520 --> 00:26:18,120
That's the easy part.

396
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:21,200
They call this part of Fifth Avenue, Carnegie Hill.

397
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:24,120
You've got the park right across the street, and the reservoir.

398
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,880
Best jogging in New York.

399
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:27,720
Mount Sinai Hospital is up the street.

400
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:29,480
Some excellent schools.

401
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:33,080
Not on the top of Mr. Milton's list
when he bought this building...

402
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:35,600
but great neighborhood for children.

403
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:37,000
Great building.

404
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:40,640
Follow the money all the way to the top.

405
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:44,160
You've got the managing director, Eddie Barzoon, on 16.

406
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:47,040
And, of course, Mr. Milton has the tower.

407
00:26:50,320 --> 00:26:52,120
- You must be Mary Ann?
- Yes, I am.

408
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:54,520
Welcome. I'm Jackie Heath.

409
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:57,440
It's nice of you to come by.

410
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:59,840
Oh, please. We Live across the hall.

411
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:01,960
- You're kidding.
- Right there.

412
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:04,400
It's just two apartments per floor?

413
00:27:04,480 --> 00:27:08,400
- You didn't tell them about it?
- It can speak for itself.

414
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:10,880
Voila!

415
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:18,360
Oh, my God!

416
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:22,000
It's what they call a ''Classic Eight''.

417
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:24,800
Be careful. I don't have a map.
I don't want you to get Lost.

418
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:29,320
We had them paint it white. Let you see it
naked before you pick your palette.

419
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,640
What am I picking?

420
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:32,120
Palette. Your colors.

421
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:33,200
Oh, yes.

422
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:37,960
I need to warn you about one thing.

423
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:42,040
There are going to be some very envious
people down at the firm.

424
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:45,840
There aren't many of these apartments.
They're a partner's perk.

425
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:48,200
You must've made quite an impression.

426
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:52,160
Oh, my God, three bedrooms.
You know what that means?

427
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:53,840
Bables.

428
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:56,240
It took us six years to get in here.

429
00:28:00,440 --> 00:28:02,000
Unbelievable.

430
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:05,600
Thank you very much.

431
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:11,960
Are you really this good?

432
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:14,680
I sure as hell hope so.

433
00:28:16,040 --> 00:28:18,040
They must want you pretty bad.

434
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,040
Look, Mar...

435
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:25,280
I'm only getting behind this if you're on board.

436
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:27,280
If you want to go home...

437
00:28:27,960 --> 00:28:29,280
I'm with you.

438
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:30,720
Sure.

439
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:34,200
Let's go back to Gainesville, back to the condo.

440
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:38,760
You keep scrounging for clients and I'll
keep repossessing cars for Akamian.

441
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:42,400
And maybe, just maybe, if we kill ourselves...

442
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:48,080
in about five years we can afford a baby
and a weekend shack at Gulf Shores.

443
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:50,240
Are you shitting me?

444
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:57,240
I Love you.

445
00:28:57,840 --> 00:28:59,400
I Love you, too.

446
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:05,480
Tadashi Osumi, Media.

447
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:07,600
Walter Krasna, Maritime Law.

448
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:09,840
Bashir Toabal, Energy Law.

449
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:11,680
I run the Islamic subgroup.

